snippet: A string of explosions on the island over the weekend left no reported injuries, but many residents and foreign embassies were concerned.
abstract: Residents of semi-autonomous Tanzanian island of Zanzibar fear string of small bombings are directly result of controversial ruling by election commission canceling results from local elections held at end of October due to allegations of fraud.

byline.contributor: Jeffrey Gettleman contributed reporting from Nairobi, Kenya.

lead_paragraph: A string of explosions on the island over the weekend left no reported injuries, but many residents and foreign embassies were concerned.

headline.main: Zanzibar Bombings May Be Related to a Disputed Election
headline.print_headline: Blasts on Tanzania Island Could Be Tied to Election
